ceted story of the United States during a transformative period. Its narrative approach, combined with scholarly updates and inclusive perspectives, positions it as a strong contender in the field of American history education.</p>\n<p>While it may not replace specialized monographs for advanced research, its role as an introductory yet comprehensive text is well established. As American history continues to evolve as a discipline, Shi’s volume reflects an ongoing commitment to presenting history as a dynamic story shaped by diverse actors and complex forces.</p>",
